        "title": "Add Swedish control UI locale",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add Swedish (`sv`) as a supported control UI locale\n- generate and register `ui/src/i18n/locales/sv.ts` against the current 1118-key source locale set\n- preserve the newer `ar`, `it`, `vi`, `nl`, and `fa` locale registrations while syncing metadata and language labels\n- update registry tests for the expanded locale list and Swedish browser locale detection, including `sv-SE`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Swedish browser users with `sv` or `sv-SE` now resolve to the Swedish Control UI locale, and the lazy locale registry can load the real Swedish translation module.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `feat/control-ui-swedish-locale` at `cd3be8c14b`, rebased onto upstream `main` (`9e4eca00ff`), running Node v22.22.2 with repo dependencies installed by pnpm.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Imported the actual Control UI registry and Swedish locale module from the checked-out branch and resolved Swedish browser language values without mocks:\n\n```console\nnode --import tsx --input-type=module -e 'import { resolveNavigatorLocale, loadLazyLocaleTranslation, SUPPORTED_LOCALES } from \"./ui/src/i18n/lib/registry.ts\"; const sv=await loadLazyLocaleTranslation(\"sv\"); console.log(JSON.stringify({ hasSv: SUPPORTED_LOCALES.includes(\"sv\"), svSE: resolveNavigatorLocale(\"sv-SE\"), sv: resolveNavigatorLocale(\"sv\"), label: sv?.languages?.sv, commonHealth: sv?.common?.health }, null, 2));'\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the real local checkout:\n\n```console\n{\n  \"hasSv\": true,\n  \"svSE\": \"sv\",\n  \"sv\": \"sv\",\n  \"label\": \"Svenska\",\n  \"commonHealth\": \"Status\"\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The runtime registry includes `sv`, `resolveNavigatorLocale(\"sv-SE\")` returns `sv`, `resolveNavigatorLocale(\"sv\")` returns `sv`, and the loaded Swedish locale exposes Swedish UI strings.\n\n**What was not tested:** No known gaps for this registry/lazy-locale behavior. Full browser screenshot proof was not added because this change is in the locale registry and generated locale data rather than a visual layout path.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts src/i18n/registry.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- committed diff credential-pattern scan found no secret material\n\n## Notes\n- the Swedish locale now matches the current source key shape; untranslated newer strings are tracked as fallback keys by the existing i18n metadata flow\n",
